# Organize repo by feature

- **Feature-first**: group by domain (`src/features/billing/`) over generic buckets. `utils/`, `components/` are for cross-feature code only.
- **One purpose per folder**: a folder answers "what lives here?" in one sentence.
- **Stable boundaries**: cross-feature imports go through public entry points (`index.ts`, `mod.rs`, `__init__.py`)—not deep paths.
- **Naming**: kebab-case unless the language dictates otherwise (PascalCase React components, snake_case Python).
- **No junk in root**: keep root for top-level configs, `README`, `LICENSE`, tooling.
- **Tests next to code** or mirrored under `tests/`—pick one per repo.
- **Delete dead paths**: remove unused folders and generated artifacts; `.gitignore` instead of versioning.

```text
src/
├── features/
│   ├── billing/
│   │   ├── api.ts
│   │   ├── billing.test.ts
│   │   └── index.ts
│   └── auth/
│       ├── login.ts
│       └── index.ts
├── shared/
│   ├── http.ts
│   └── logger.ts
└── index.ts
```
